KB004 — How to Check Windows Update Health
Purpose:  
Help technicians diagnose update failures, stuck installations, and systems requiring servicing stack repair.

🧭 Steps
Check Update History  
Settings → Windows Update → Update History

Check Servicing Stack  
Look for repeated failures or rollback loops.

Check Windows Update Service  
Ensure wuauserv is running.

Check Disk Space  
Updates fail with < 10% free space.

Check Event Logs  
Review WindowsUpdateClient logs.

Run DISM Health Check

Code
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth
Run SFC Scan

Code
sfc /scannow
